                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Here is my take on Charm  and CC......
<br />

<br />
SOE built it.
<br />
SOE broke it.
<br />
SOE took it away.
<br />

<br />
Pi#@ poor planning leads to a Pi#@ poor product.
<br />

<br />
BUT....  
<br />

<br />
I made an ench to be needed
<br />
I charmed my way thru many levels because it was FUN and hence EQ was FUN !!
<br />
I CC'd in groups because I felt like a god when I saved the day and EQ was FUN !!
<br />
I joined a Raiding guild and could use both skills, and EQ was FUN !!
<br />

<br />
Charm is dead.    <img src="images/smiles/icon_cry.gif" alt="icon_cry.gif" border="0" /> 
<br />
CC is dead.   <img src="images/smiles/icon_cry.gif" alt="icon_cry.gif" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />

<br />
My Enchanter lies unused and retired basically, and EQ is no longer FUN.
<br />

<br />
SOE needs to realize (Homer Simpson DOH !) that this is simply a GAME.  Did they forget that ?!?!  The great players are always going to find ways to exploit things.  Minimize the effects and move on.  Don't ruin entire classes with the nerf bat.
<br />

<br />
Additionally, I believe a company should stand behind its product.  If I was sold a kit to build a house and told that the roof would keep me dry and I spent 5 years building it and then the company who I had paid for the kit called and said 
<br />

<br />
"Oh by the way the roof design is faulty and will leak.  You better either build a new house or pay me more money for the real roof"
<br />

<br />
I would take them to court.  Granted this is only a game, but  my money isn't.  SOE needs to stop trying to rush out each new release to make a buck and test their products better.  
<br />

<br />
I posted my long answer on Juwel's Charm thread months ago  -- but  basically it boils down to Broken mobs/xp rewards -- not broken classes.  This class was great during Kunark, Velious and early PoP.  Level 45-65 was truly a blast.  In fact if you rerolled an Ench just before the last charm nerf -- the class is still pretty fun to play Up till level 60~65 in certain zones.  Ask yourself what changed significantly for Enc's since then?  Did our ability to take Damage change much --NO.  Did our ability to deal damage outside of charm change much? -- NO.  Did anything inherent to our Class change significantly in a truly unbalanced kind of way? -- NO.  
<br />

<br />
  What did change?  simply stated, the mobs !!!  Their HPs/AC and DPS scaled way to fast.  Why did SOE go this route?  Because any other route would have required inventive and imaginative thinking to make encounters feel fresh, and they believe in large part that a new release has to feel fresh.  This is their first mistake.  It was so easy for them to simply copy, cut and paste the code for mob "dire wolf" from GD and add a zero behind the number of HP's and the Mobs AC and then rename the mob Rockhopper in DSP".  Then they could spend all their time on the new graphics engine etc.. things that could help them get other projects like EQ2 up and running faster.  
<br />

<br />
Secondly, SOE doesn't truly understand their customer base physchology very well.  There are basically two types of players.  The raid player is the customer that truly needs the inventive, imaginative encounters.  The casual player likes the group grind or Solo grind.  As long as the XP bar seems to move at an appropriate rate then they are happy to sit at a camp and grind.  Yes there are better camps than others but basically it is Grinding Xp AKA the old text versions  of MMPORGS.
<br />
 
<br />
If SOE had placed their time and souls into the raid encounters to make them interesting and challenging while at the same time simply scaling the casual players mobs more appropriately in each expansion to match the paltry upgrade to PC skills -- <span style="font-weight: bold">then Charm and CC would be IDENTICAL at Level 70 with 100's of AA's versus level 60</span>. 
<br />

<br />
Unfortunately, they didn't and the hasted charmed mob's DPS was throw totally out of whack.  
<br />

<br />
Then they compounded their mistake.  Instead of properly identifying the problem and choosing to fix it the right way -- they misidentified the problem or chose to implement a fast fix -- enter the Class Nerf bat.
<br />

<br />
Am I down on SOE -- Yes.
<br />

<br />
Why?  Because appropriately scaling mobs accessible to the casual player would have been so easy.  They could have made this game continue to be FUN for all players with the appropriate use of scaling and placement of mobs.  I truly feel they have rushed the last few expansions to release -- NOT from a game stability standpoint but from a content and class balance perspective.  
<br />

<br />

<br />
I don't believe that with any amount of discussion or threads these issues will ever change significantly.  I would love to be surprised but have no hopes in this regard.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
I feel WET !!  My roof has many leaks.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
