                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I understand your points Yakk...
<br />

<br />
1)  Did Tank durability increase first or mob DPS?  It's the old-- which came first?  the chicken or the egg quandry.   In either case, how can SOE justify scaling mob DPS or Tank durability out of proportion to every other class durability? ( in particular Enc)  This is exactly the scaling type fault I believe is the underliying problem.  Why not simply scale-up Mob DPS and/or Tank durability proportionately in the context of the other class advances?,  That way most other classes don't get left behind in this regard?
<br />

<br />
2)  I don't deny that their have been some great and innovative Group encounters written for the game...and I applaud those developers and coders.   Also, I don't deny that there are players that enjoy them, but get serious...the majority of players don't spend their online time in those "15 interesting group encounters" you speak of.  Do a /who while you are /LFG nowadays and see what zones peeps are in.  They are in the XP grind zones -- the "hot" Zones -- or in raids.  I have a hot button set up to check level ranges of peeps online when I log on.  
<br />

<br />
3)  Yes, our spells LOST some of their effectiveness so I guess we agree on this point.  To clarify I should have said 
<br />

<br />
Did anything inherent to our Class (<span style="font-weight: bold">ENC</span>) change significantly in a truly unbalanced kind of way? -- NO.  (meaning to <span style="font-weight: bold">OUR</span> advantage)
<br />

<br />

<br />
Anyway..my 2 cps</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
